(4, 1, '2010-06-30 10:14:40', '2010-06-30 10:14:40', 'The history of the internet is one of evolution in technology and revolution in daily life. From its humble beginnings in 1957, through  the dot-com crash of the 90''s and todays web of convenience: the best online ideas survive, the weak fail. So, have a pint and join us for some of the fittest ideas in true Darwinian spirit in the birthplace of evolutionary thought, Shrewsbury.', 'The Theory of (R)Evolution?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-theory-of-revolution', '', '', '2010-07-11 14:59:01', '2010-07-11 14:59:01', '', 0, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/?p=4', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(185, 1, '2010-07-09 21:53:57', '2010-07-09 21:53:57', '<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/muprofileicon.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-72" title="muprofileicon" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/muprofileicon-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>Web developer for The Guardian newspaper, Dan is also the man behind The Guardian Zeitgeist.\r\n\r\nWith the decline in print sales and increase in online media all of the national newspapers have to evolve to stay a float. The Guardian newspaper is no exception.\r\n\r\nDan will discuss how the Guardian is evoloving with it''s Open Platform, APIs, digital journalism and good old pragmatic programming.\r\n\r\nHe''ll probably also gossip wildly about Yahoo, the start-up scene in San Francisco and a bit about Pandas.', 'Dan Catt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-12', '', '', '2010-07-09 21:53:57', '2010-07-09 21:53:57', '', 18, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/18-revision-12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
