(106, 1, '2010-07-11 10:09:11', '2010-07-11 10:09:11', '<h3>Heather Noble</h3>\n<img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-128" title="twitterProfilePhoto" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/twitterProfilePhoto-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" />Salt Solutions is a Shropshire based company established by local business woman <strong>Heather Noble</strong> in 2009. Their aim is to help small to medium sized businesses raise their profile via effective event planning.\n\nWith over 20 years experience across a broad range of business sectors Heather established Salt to utilise her considerable marketing, organisation and planning skills to support others who just don''t have the time or experience to coordinate and plan effectively and successfully.\n\nIf you are keen to work with honest, professionals who have bundles of enthusiasm, integrity, creative flair and an eye for detail just add a pinch of Salt…\n\nCall 07843 006984 to find out more about our services.\n\nYou can also <a href="http://www.salt-solutions.co.uk/" target="_blank">visit the website</a> or follow <a href="http://twitter.com/salt_events" target="_blank">Heather on twitter</a>\n<h3>Kirsty Burgoine</h3>\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/n1104498633_3060.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-109" title="Kirsty Burgoine" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/n1104498633_3060-150x150.jpg" alt="Kirsty Burgoine" width="150" height="150" /></a>Kirsty Burgoine is a freelance web developer based in Shrewsbury, Shropshire.\n\nWith 10 years experience working for marketing, print and web design studios throughout Shropshire. Kirsty has an excellent understanding of what it takes to create a successful website, including initial design and build, search engine optimization and online marketing.\n\nIn 2010 Kirsty set up as a freelancer. Using her experience developing both small lead generation brochure sites and large scale, bespoke e-commerce solutions, she now specializes in developing for Wordpress. Focusing on websites for small independent, companies and new business startups.\n\nAs well as this, Kirsty is the editor <a href="http://www.creativeboom.co.uk/shrewsbury">Creative Boom Shrewsbury</a>. An online magazine designed to celebrate, inspire and support the creative industries throughout Shropshire.\n\nTo find out more information visit her website <a href="http://www.kirstyburgoine.co.uk/">www.kirstyburgoine.co.uk</a> or follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/kirstyburgoine">Kirsty on twitter</a>\n<h3>Zach Beauvais</h3>\n<img class="alignleft" title="Zach Beauvais" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/phpThumb_generated_thumbnailjpg1.jpg" alt="Zach Beauvais" width="150" height="150" />Zach is one of the original founders of Shropgeek and regular attendee\n\nZach Beauvais works for Talis as a Platform Evangelist: talking, reading and writing about the semantic web, Linked Data and online innovation.\n\nWith a background in linguistics, Zach is interested in semantics first, and the web second; seeing the advantage of building with machine-readable data.\n\nHe has written for ReadWriteWeb and ZDNet, he also edits the Semantic Web''s community magazine, <a href="http://blogs.talis.com/nodalities/">Nodalities</a> and regularly records podcasts for Nodalities\n\nYou can find out more by reading his blog, <a href="http://www.zachbeauvais.com/">Blogging Perspective</a> or you can follow Zach on twitter\n\nOr to find out more about Talis visit their website <a href="http://www.talis.com/platform/">www.talis.com/platform/</a>', 'The Organisers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '104-autosave', '', '', '2010-07-11 10:09:11', '2010-07-11 10:09:11', '', 104, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/104-autosave', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
