(142, 1, '2010-07-08 00:13:20', '2010-07-08 00:13:20', 'The Shropshire Geek Society was originally started 18 months ago by Zach Beauvais and Dean (Leu) Thorne, The idea was simple. A tweetup once a month for like minded geeks from around Shropshire.\r\n\r\nSadly Leu passed away on 18<sup>th</sup> September 2009. However, after a break, a fellow regular Kirsty Burgoine stepped in to help organize the tweetups.\r\n\r\nMostly publicized through twitter, shropgeek is a relaxed evening of beer and geekery. Held on the 1st Friday of every month at the Admiral Benbow in Shrewsbury. It is a great opportunity for people working in all industries to get together and socialize.\r\n\r\nYou can find out a bit more information by visiting the website: <a href="http://www.shropgeek.co.uk" target="_blank">www.shropgeek.co.uk</a>\r\n\r\nOr by following us on twitter: <a href="http://www.twitter.com/shropgeek" target="_blank">@shropgeek</a>', 'About Shropgeek', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-6', '', '', '2010-07-08 00:13:20', '2010-07-08 00:13:20', '', 2, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/2-revision-6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
