(196, 1, '2010-07-10 19:51:25', '2010-07-10 19:51:25', '<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482.jpg"><img src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482-225x300.jpg" alt="Shropgeek" title="Shropgeek" width="225" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-141" /></a>Shropgeek was originally started 18 months ago by Zach Beauvais and Dean (Leu) Thorne, The idea was simple. A ''tweetup'' once a month for like minded geeks from around Shropshire.\r\n\r\nOriginally, meetings were held in different towns but it quickly became apparent that Shrewsbury was the easiest location for everyone to attend.\r\n\r\nSadly Leu passed away on 18<sup>th</sup> September 2009. However, after a break, a fellow regular Kirsty Burgoine stepped in to help organize the tweetups.\r\n\r\nMostly publicized through twitter, Shropgeek meet ups are held on the 1st Friday of every month at the Admiral Benbow in Shrewsbury. The evenings start at 7.30pm and are a great opportunity for people working in all industries to get together and socialize with no pressure of networking.\r\n\r\nEach month people from all areas of the IT industry meet up for a relaxed evening of beer and chat. There are no speeches or sales pitches, just like minded individuals sitting in a pub discussing the current events within the IT and web industries.\r\n\r\nThe next three monthly meet ups will be:\r\n\r\nFriday 6th August\r\nFriday 3rd September\r\nFriday 1st October\r\n\r\n<strong>Anybody is welcome to come along. The only criteria for joining in with Shropgeek is you have to show up!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can find out a bit more information and see reviews of previous meetups by visiting the website: <a href="http://www.shropgeek.co.uk" target="_blank">www.shropgeek.co.uk</a>\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can follow us on twitter: <a href="http://www.twitter.com/shropgeek" target="_blank">@shropgeek</a>', 'About Shropgeek', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-18', '', '', '2010-07-10 19:51:25', '2010-07-10 19:51:25', '', 2, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/2-revision-18', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(200, 1, '2010-07-09 23:26:13', '2010-07-09 23:26:13', '<h3>Dan Catt</h3>\r\n<img class="alignleft" title="Dan Catt" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/muprofileicon.jpg" alt="Dan Catt" width="150" height="150" />Dan spent 4 years working for Flickr during which time he learnt quite a bit about scaling, passionate user communities, what makes a 4 Billion photo website tick and even a bit about photography.\r\n\r\nHe''s returned to the UK as a developer for the Guardian newspaper splitting his time between Shrewsbury and London. With the decline in print sales and increase in online media all of the national newspapers have to change to stay a float. The Guardian newspaper is no exception.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>Katy Cowan</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/Katy-Cowan1-150x1501.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-53" title="Katy Cowan" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/Katy-Cowan1-150x1501.jpg" alt="Katy Cowan" width="150" height="150" /></a>Katy is a former broadcast journalist who studied Journalism at University of Central Lancashire, graduating in 2000. She started her career working for Signal Radio in Stoke-on-Trent before moving on to Saga Radio in Birmingham. After five years of reading the news live on the airwaves - and interviewing big names like Will Smith and various politians - Katy needed a fresh challenge and went into the world of public relations, securing a job at the North West''s leading PR agencies, Citypress. After three fantastic years in Manchester , a niggling health problem forced Katy to go freelance and she started her own business, Boomerang PR in August 2007. Up until March 2009, business was booming. But then the recession hit and Katy lost many clients.\r\n\r\nThat was when Katy came up with the idea of Creative Boom, an online magazine for the creative industries throughout the UK. She wanted to raise her profile, attract new business and network while helping other freelancers to do the same. \r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>Zach Beauvais</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/phpThumb_generated_thumbnailjpg1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-54" title="Zach Beauvais" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/phpThumb_generated_thumbnailjpg1-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>Zach has written for ReadWriteWeb and ZDNet, and is most interested in the potential of Linked Data to change the way the web is done. He edits the Semantic Web''s community magazine, Nodalities, and works as Talis'' Platform Evangelist.\r\n\r\nWith a background in linguistics, Zach is interested in semantics first, and the web second; seeing the advantage of building with machine-readable data. RDF is fascinating, as it''s a way to model what we know in a way which is not only extremely expressive (almost linguistic) but, like a language, also extensible.\r\n\r\nTying together Open Data with the Semantic Web is one of the most important goals on the web. With web standards, like RDF and HTTP, the web can give the wider community access to knowledge of increasing granularity and complexity; and it''s at the joins that we see interesting innovation. So, to this end, Zach has been writing more about the Semantic Web at Talis, and works with the Platform team to host events, raise awareness, and train up innovators. He''s also a drummer...', 'The Speakers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-revision-17', '', '', '2010-07-09 23:26:13', '2010-07-09 23:26:13', '', 14, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/14-revision-17', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(199, 1, '2010-07-11 10:14:24', '2010-07-11 10:14:24', '<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482.jpg"><img src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482-225x300.jpg" alt="Shropgeek" title="Shropgeek" width="225" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-141" /></a>Shropgeek was originally started 18 months ago by Zach Beauvais and Dean (Leu) Thorne, The idea was simple. A ''tweetup'' once a month for like minded geeks from around Shropshire.\r\n\r\nSadly Leu passed away on 18<sup>th</sup> September 2009. However, after a break, a fellow regular Kirsty Burgoine stepped in to help organize the tweetups.\r\n\r\nMostly publicized through twitter, Shropgeek meet ups are held on the 1st Friday of every month at the Admiral Benbow in Shrewsbury. The evenings start at 7.30pm and are a great opportunity for people working in all industries to get together and socialize with no pressure of networking.\r\n\r\nEach month people from all areas of the IT industry come together, and enjoy a relaxed evening of beer and chat. There are no speeches or sales pitches, just like minded individuals sitting in a pub discussing the current events within the IT and web industries.\r\n\r\nThe next three monthly meet ups will be:\r\n\r\nFriday 6th August 2010\r\nFriday 3rd September 2010\r\nFriday 1st October 2010\r\n\r\n<strong>Anybody is welcome to come along. The only criteria for joining in with Shropgeek is you have to show up!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can find out a bit more information and see reviews of previous meetups by visiting the website: <a href="http://www.shropgeek.co.uk" target="_blank">www.shropgeek.co.uk</a>\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can follow us on twitter: <a href="http://www.twitter.com/shropgeek" target="_blank">@shropgeek</a>', 'About Shropgeek', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-21', '', '', '2010-07-11 10:14:24', '2010-07-11 10:14:24', '', 2, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/2-revision-21', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(201, 1, '2010-07-09 22:55:50', '2010-07-09 22:55:50', '<h3>The Boathouse</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/the-boathouse1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-159" style="margin-top: 20px;" title="the boathouse" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/the-boathouse1.jpg" alt="The Boathouse" width="600" height="260" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Boathouse is one of those well known pubs that everyone enjoys visiting. </strong>\r\n\r\nSat on the banks of the River Severn and overlooking Shrewsbury''s idyllic Quarry park, the Boathouse has something for everyone, including the best beer garden in the County, a function room, good food, including a carvery and that Olde Worldy feel to the bar.\r\n\r\nLocal cask ales are also sold, including beers from the Salopian Brewery, Woods Brewery and other Shrophire Brewers.\r\n\r\nGetting to it couldn''t be easier. It can be accessed from the road or through The Quarry. It is within easy reach of the town centre and all central car parks and Shrewsbury train station is only 15 minutes away.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Boathouse</strong>\r\nNew Street\r\nShrewsbury\r\nShropshire\r\nSY3 8JQ\r\n\r\nTel: 01743 231658\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theboathouse-shrewsbury.co.uk/" target="_blank">Visit the website</a>', 'Venue', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-26', '', '', '2010-07-09 22:55:50', '2010-07-09 22:55:50', '', 16, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/16-revision-26', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(202, 1, '2010-07-11 10:11:13', '2010-07-11 10:11:13', '<h3>Heather Noble</h3>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-128" title="twitterProfilePhoto" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/twitterProfilePhoto-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" />Salt Solutions is a Shropshire based company established by local business woman <strong>Heather Noble</strong> in 2009. Their aim is to help small to medium sized businesses raise their profile via effective event planning.\r\n\r\nWith over 20 years experience across a broad range of business sectors Heather established Salt to utilise her considerable marketing, organisation and planning skills to support others who just don''t have the time or experience to coordinate and plan effectively and successfully.\r\n\r\nIf you are keen to work with honest, professionals who have bundles of enthusiasm, integrity, creative flair and an eye for detail just add a pinch of Salt…\r\n\r\nCall 07843 006984 to find out more about our services.\r\n\r\nYou can also <a href="http://www.salt-solutions.co.uk/" target="_blank">visit the website</a> or follow <a href="http://twitter.com/salt_events" target="_blank">Heather on twitter</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>Kirsty Burgoine</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/n1104498633_3060.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-109" title="Kirsty Burgoine" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/n1104498633_3060-150x150.jpg" alt="Kirsty Burgoine" width="150" height="150" /></a>Kirsty Burgoine is a freelance web developer based in Shrewsbury, Shropshire.\r\n\r\nWith 10 years experience working for marketing, print and web design studios throughout Shropshire. Kirsty has an excellent understanding of what it takes to create a successful website, including initial design and build, search engine optimization and online marketing.\r\n\r\nIn 2010 Kirsty set up as a freelancer. Using her experience developing both small lead generation brochure sites and large scale, bespoke e-commerce solutions, she now specializes in developing for Wordpress. Focusing on websites for small independent, companies and new business startups.\r\n\r\nAs well as this, Kirsty is the editor <a href="http://www.creativeboom.co.uk/shrewsbury">Creative Boom Shrewsbury</a>. An online magazine designed to celebrate, inspire and support the creative industries throughout Shropshire.\r\n\r\nTo find out more information visit her website <a href="http://www.kirstyburgoine.co.uk/">www.kirstyburgoine.co.uk</a> or follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/kirstyburgoine">Kirsty on twitter</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>Zach Beauvais</h3>\r\n<img class="alignleft" title="Zach Beauvais" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/phpThumb_generated_thumbnailjpg1.jpg" alt="Zach Beauvais" width="150" height="150" />Zach is one of the original founders of Shropgeek and regular attendee\r\n\r\nZach Beauvais works for Talis as a Platform Evangelist: talking, reading and writing about the semantic web, Linked Data and online innovation.\r\n\r\nWith a background in linguistics, Zach is interested in semantics first, and the web second; seeing the advantage of building with machine-readable data.\r\n\r\nHe has written for ReadWriteWeb and ZDNet, he also edits the Semantic Web''s community magazine, <a href="http://blogs.talis.com/nodalities/">Nodalities</a> and regularly records podcasts for Nodalities\r\n\r\nYou can find out more by reading Zach''s blog, <a href="http://www.zachbeauvais.com/">Blogging Perspective</a> or you can follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/zbeauvais" target="_blank">Zach on twitter</a>\r\n\r\nTo find out more about Talis visit their website <a href="http://www.talis.com/platform/">www.talis.com/platform/</a>', 'The Organisers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '104-revision-21', '', '', '2010-07-11 10:11:13', '2010-07-11 10:11:13', '', 104, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/104-revision-21', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
