(204, 1, '2010-07-09 23:57:10', '2010-07-09 23:57:10', '<span style="font-size: 1.3em;">The Theory of (R)Evolution is an evening of talks by some of the most innovative people working within the web today.</span>\r\n\r\nHeld at The Boathouse, Shrewsbury, the evening will consist of three talks by experts within their specialist fields.\r\n\r\n<strong>Zach Beauvais</strong> - will discuss the potential of Linked Data, how its implementation will revolutionize the way websites work, and how its already being implemented by the likes of wikipedia and the BBC. \r\n\r\n<strong>Katy Cowan </strong>- will talk about how Creative Boom was born and how its success has helped struggling artists and freelancers and in turn helped her own business thrive.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dan Catt </strong>- will discuss how the Guardian is evolving with it''s Open Platform, APIs, digital journalism and good old pragmatic programming.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1.3em;">Why put on an event?</span>\r\n\r\nThe web industry is one of the few areas that continues to grow despite the recession. However, web events and seminars are becoming less affordable each year. As the amount of people working within the web industry continues to spread, one area of the country seems to remain largely forgotten. \r\n\r\nShropshire has a thriving IT industry, so Shropgeek decided to give something back!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1.3em;">Doors open at 6pm, with the first speaker starting at 6.30pm</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1.3em;">Early Bird tickets cost £10. Normal ticket price £15.</span>\r\n\r\nTicket prices cover the cost of the Venue and marketing materials. Any profit after that will be donated to a charity chosen on the night.', 'The Event', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-12', '', '', '2010-07-09 23:57:10', '2010-07-09 23:57:10', '', 12, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/12-revision-12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
