(408, 1, '2010-08-18 19:11:48', '2010-08-18 19:11:48', '<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482.jpg"><img src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/IMG_0482-225x300.jpg" alt="Shropgeek" title="Shropgeek" width="225" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-141" /></a>Shropgeek was originally started 18 months ago by Zach Beauvais and Dean (Leu) Thorne, The idea was simple. A ''tweetup'' once a month for like-minded geeks from around Shropshire. The definition of a geek was always seen as a loose one, welcoming anyone with that spark of the hacker about them: from developers and designers to enthusiasts and creative-types. It was a bit of an experiment to see how many fellow geeks there were, and the results were phenomenal: Shropshire has a lot of interesting people!\r\n\r\nSadly Leu passed away on 18<sup>th</sup> September 2009. However, after a break, a fellow regular Kirsty Burgoine stepped in to help organize the tweetups.\r\n\r\nMostly publicized through <a href="http://twitter.com/shropgeek">twitter</a>, Shropgeeks get together on the 1st Friday of every month at the Admiral Benbow in Shrewsbury. The evenings start at 7.30pm and are a great opportunity for people working in all industries to socialize with no pressure of networking.\r\n\r\nThere is no fixed agenda, though topics are often suggested on twitter. The idea is to have a friendly catch-up from across the web, IT and adjoining industries with some beery banter and cheerful chat. \r\n\r\nThe next three monthly meet ups will be:\r\n\r\nFriday 6th August 2010\r\nFriday 10th September 2010\r\nFriday 1st October 2010\r\n\r\n<strong>Anybody is welcome to come along. The only criteria for joining in with Shropgeek is you have to show up!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can find out a bit more information and see reviews of previous meetups by visiting the website: <a href="http://www.shropgeek.co.uk" target="_blank">www.shropgeek.co.uk</a>\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can follow us on twitter: <a href="http://www.twitter.com/shropgeek" target="_blank">@shropgeek</a>', 'About Shropgeek', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-24', '', '', '2010-08-18 19:11:48', '2010-08-18 19:11:48', '', 2, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/2-revision-24', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(409, 1, '2010-07-11 15:16:31', '2010-07-11 15:16:31', '<h3>The Boathouse</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/the-boathouse1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-159" style="margin-top: 20px;" title="the boathouse" src="http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/the-boathouse1.jpg" alt="The Boathouse" width="600" height="260" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Boathouse is one of those well known pubs that everyone enjoys visiting. </strong>\r\n\r\nSat on the banks of the River Severn and overlooking Shrewsbury''s idyllic Quarry park, the Boathouse has something for everyone, including the best beer garden in the county, a function room, good food (including a carvery) and that Olde Worldy feel to the bar.\r\n\r\nLocal cask ales are also sold, including beers from the Salopian Brewery, Woods Brewery and other Shrophire Brewers.\r\n\r\nGetting to it couldn''t be easier. It can be accessed on foot from the road or through The Quarry. It is within easy reach of the town centre and all central car parks. Shrewsbury train station is only 15 minutes away.\r\n\r\n<iframe width="300" height="290" class="alignright" style="margin-right: 20px;" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" src="http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=SY3+8JQ&amp;sll=53.800651,-4.064941&amp;sspn=17.287903,39.506836&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=Shrewsbury,+Shropshire+SY3+5,+United+Kingdom&amp;ll=52.709883,-2.762718&amp;spn=0.0156,0.025749&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=A&amp;output=embed"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Boathouse</strong>\r\nNew Street\r\nShrewsbury\r\nShropshire\r\nSY3 8JQ\r\n\r\nTel: 01743 231658\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theboathouse-shrewsbury.co.uk/" target="_blank">Visit the website</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Venue', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-35', '', '', '2010-07-11 15:16:31', '2010-07-11 15:16:31', '', 16, 'http://www.shropgeek-revolution.co.uk/uncategorized/16-revision-35', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
